BC-250 / Cyan Skillfish: enable clock gating (idle power)

AMD ships cyan skillfish with cg_flags=0/pg_flags=0 and leaves its IP
revisions (GC 10.1.3/4, SDMA 5.0.1, NBIF 2.1.1, MMHUB/ATHUB 2.0.3) out
of every set_clockgating_state switch, so no clock in the chip ever
gates at idle (~20 W on VDDCR_GFX at 0% activity). The silicon is
navi1x-generation; this mirrors Navi10's CG set minus VCN/JPEG (not
present) and BIF (NBIF 2.1.1 register map unvalidated), and adds the
missing switch cases. Each update func is flag-gated, so features can
be bisected at boot with amdgpu.cg_mask (GFX-only: 0x5).

The navi1x MGCG TCP_CTRL workaround is deliberately NOT applied: its
register lists encode Navi10/12 WGP topology. If GFX misbehaves under
load with MGCG, drop bit 0 via cg_mask before suspecting anything else.

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/nv.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/nv.c
@@ -870,7 +870,23 @@
 		break;
 	case IP_VERSION(10, 1, 3):
 	case IP_VERSION(10, 1, 4):
-		adev->cg_flags = 0;
+		/* BC-250 (cyan skillfish): never validated by AMD, but the
+		 * silicon is navi1x-generation GC 10.1; mirror Navi10's CG
+		 * set minus the IPs this part lacks (VCN/JPEG) and BIF
+		 * (NBIF 2.1.1 unvalidated). Bisect at boot via
+		 * amdgpu.cg_mask if instability appears.
+		 */
+		adev->cg_flags = AMD_CG_SUPPORT_GFX_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_GFX_CGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_IH_CG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_HDP_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_HDP_LS |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_SDMA_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_SDMA_LS |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_MC_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_MC_LS |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_ATHUB_MGCG |
+			AMD_CG_SUPPORT_ATHUB_LS;
 		adev->pg_flags = 0;
 		adev->external_rev_id = adev->rev_id + 0x82;
 		break;
@@ -1049,6 +1065,7 @@
 		return 0;
 
 	switch (amdgpu_ip_version(adev, NBIO_HWIP, 0)) {
+	case IP_VERSION(2, 1, 1):
 	case IP_VERSION(2, 3, 0):
 	case IP_VERSION(2, 3, 1):
 	case IP_VERSION(2, 3, 2):
